import requests

# Search PDB for human p53 structures
search_url = "https://search.rcsb.org/rcsbsearch/v2/query"

query = {
    "query": {
        "type": "terminal",
        "service": "full_text",
        "parameters": {"value": "p53 DNA binding human"}
    },
    "return_type": "entry",
    "request_options": {
        "paginate": {"start": 0, "rows": 5}
    }
}

response = requests.post(search_url, json=query)
results = response.json()

pdb_ids = [r['identifier'] for r in results['result_set']]
print("Found PDB entries:", pdb_ids)

The goal of this section is to build an AI agent that can analyze protein data and generate drug discovery hypotheses step by step.

When you understand the basic workflow, you will be able to design and build your own agents.

Let’s start with installing dependencies and loading API keys below. We will be using the Anthropic native tool use in this example, so make sure you have an Anthropic API key.

